          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              I just got a Razer DeathAdder and I love it. Previously I had an MS Intellimouse 3.0a that last a long, long time that I loved. When it broke I replaced it with a Logitech MX518. That was a great mouse but lasted a disappointing 2 years before the cord started to short out and disconnect all the time. <BR><BR>I wasn't even considering a Razer since I always considered them kinda gimmicky. I played with a Mamba in a store, though, and it felt great in my hand. However, I wasn't going to drop $130 on a mouse and I don't really care for wireless mice either. When I saw the DeathAdder was basically a wired Mamba I had to get one. It was only $60 and I payed $50 for my MX518 so it seemed like a good deal. Thankfully I picked up the DeathAdder before the Steam sale and I've been very happy with it the last month and half in L4D, Crysis, Max Payne 2, etc. Very great feel both in the hand and in game. Do sort of miss the dedicated DPI buttons my MX518 had though.<BR><BR>-Old_Wolf

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
